task.summary:
A bunch of cleanup, some minor refactoring of the selector stuff, etc.
Selector code still crashes, and I suspect that's primarily because the XML location seems off. I've moved that to the constructor in Selector class so it's easier to change, but I don't yet know how to reference files within the application that will later become local storage.

Minor UI refinements, addition of another example to our sample XML, and some more rewards handling work.
After about 90 code revisions, we can now play multiple rewards without crashing the application. Yay (really though, this API sucks)!
Fix stuck video image requiring a click to get back to menu.
Built a stub class for providing a random reward. Added multimedia displayItem support.
Added a few more notes to Dylan/Steve.
